result.execSummary:
The defendant Jonathan E. Cabral was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License (5th w/in3Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fine and Costs are to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Cash Bond and deposits previously paid have been applied to the Court Appointed Attorney's Fees.   The remaining balance of the Attorney Fees to be paid directly to the Waushara Co Clerk of Court for Court Appointed Counsel.  Attorney Fees to be paid within 60 days or set up a payment plan with the Clerk.  Failure to comply will result in contempt procedures being initiated.
Good Time Credit and Hubert Privilege granted.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
